# Welcome to the n8n Masterclass! ðŸš€

Here we'll dive into mastering the core concepts for n8n and building AI agents within it so you can feel confident getting started no matter what you want to automate!

## What is n8n?

n8n (pronounced "n-eight-n", short for nodenation) is a workflow automation platform that lets you connect apps, services, and APIs together without breaking the bank or your sanity. Think of it as the Swiss Army knife of automation - it does everything you need, and it does it well.

## Why n8n is Different

### ðŸ’° Actually Affordable
n8n is a fraction of the cost of other automation platforms like Zapier and Make.com. Also, you can self-host it on a $5/month server.

### ðŸ”“ Open Source Freedom
n8n is fair-code licensed, meaning you get the source code and can modify it however you want. No vendor lock-in, no surprise pricing changes, very little "sorry, that feature is only in our enterprise plan".

### ðŸ¤– Built for AI Agents
Here's the big one - while other platforms treat AI as an afterthought, n8n was designed with AI agents in mind. You get:
- Native AI agent nodes
- Built-in memory management
- RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) capabilities
- Vector database integrations
- Multi-agent workflows

## Why I Love n8n

- **Flexibility**: Code when you need it, visual when you don't
- **Power**: Handle complex multi-step AI workflows
- **Control**: Self-host to protect your sensitive data

## What You'll Learn Today

By the end of this session, you'll know how to:
- Navigate n8n like a pro
- Build workflows that actually solve real problems
- Create AI agents that can access your data
- Set up RAG systems that don't hallucinate

# n8n Data Types Quick Reference ðŸ“Š

Understanding data types is crucial for building workflows that actually work. We have:

## String (Text)
**What it is:** Any text data - names, emails, messages, descriptions.  
**When you see it:** Form submissions, email content, user names, file paths.
**Example:** Elon Musk, elonmusk@tesla.com, /home/elonmusk/all-secret-tesla-plans.txt

## Number
**What it is:** Numerical values for calculations and comparisons.  
**When you see it:** Prices, quantities, user IDs, timestamps, scores.
**Example:** 1000, 543532452345

## Date and Time
**What it is:** Time-based data that n8n can parse and manipulate.  
**When you see it:** Form submission times, calendar events, file creation dates, scheduled tasks.
**Example:** 2025-05-23, 2025-01-17 12:18:00, May 23rd, 2025

## Boolean
**What it is:** True/false values used for conditional logic.  
**When you see it:** Checkbox responses, status flags (active/inactive), approval states, feature toggles.
**Example:** true, false

## Array
**What it is:** A list of items - could be strings, numbers, or objects.  
**When you see it:** Multiple email recipients, list of files, search results, multiple form responses.
**Example:** [1, 2, 3, 4], ["Elon Musk", "Jeff Bezos", "Sam Altman"]

## Object (JSON)
**What it is:** Structured data with key-value pairs (like a row in a spreadsheet).  
**When you see it:** Individual form submissions, user profiles, API responses, database records.
**Example:** {"name": "Cole Medin", "interests": ["Spicy Mango", "AI"], "is_chess_grandmaster": false}

## Pro Tips
- **Arrays contain multiple items** - you'll often need to loop through them
- **Objects contain related data** - perfect for passing complete records between nodes
- **Mix and match** - Arrays can contain objects, objects can contain arrays

---

*Master these data types and n8n workflows become much easier to debug and build!*
